-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 06:33AM EDT
-- None



Sept 26 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Friday:

** Intel Corp <INTC.O> said it will pay as much as $1.5 billion for a 20 percent stake in two mobile chipmakers with ties to the Chinese government, in the hopes of catching up in a smartphone chip industry dominated by rival Qualcomm Inc <QCOM.O>. [ID:nL2N0RQ1WS]  ** Telecom Italia <TLIT.MI> should hang on to its controlling stake in Telecom Argentina <TEC2.BA>, a group of small investors said, reflecting growing unease among shareholders about a planned exit. [ID:nL6N0RR133]  ** Dallas pipeline operator Energy Transfer Partners LP <ETP.N> said it would transfer some convenience store assets within the Sunoco Inc [SUNO.UL] corporate family to Susser Petroleum Partners LP <SUSP.N> in a deal valued at about $768 million. [ID:nL3N0RR159]  ** U.S. company Chiquita <CQB.N> and Irish peer Fyffes <FFY.I> have agreed to boost Chiquita's ownership of their proposed $526 million tie-up to 59.6 percent from 50.7 percent, the companies said in a statement. [ID:nL6N0RR0LG]  ** German industrial robots maker Kuka <KU2G.DE> plans to buy Swiss logistics company Swisslog Holding <SLOG.S> for about 339 million Swiss francs ($358 million). [ID:nL2N0RQ2CC]  ** Lloyds Banking Group Plc <LLOY.L> has sold a further 11.5 percent stake in TSB Banking Group Plc <TSB.L> in a 161 million pound ($262.5 million) share placing to investors that required no discount to the market price following strong demand. [ID:nL6N0RQ4P2]  ** Japan Post Co said on Friday it has agreed to take a 40 percent stake in Saison Asset Management Co, an asset management unit of Credit Saison Co Ltd <8253.T>, a credit card company with about 35 million users. [ID:nT9N0R9025]  ** Hedge fund ValueAct Capital Management LP said on Thursday it would return to the board of directors of Valeant Pharmaceuticals International Inc <VRX.TO>, which is pursuing a hostile takeover offer for Allergan Inc <AGN.N>, and that it planned to increase its stake in the company. [ID:nL2N0RQ16D]  ** Danish telecoms group TDC <TDC.CO> said it had agreed to buy privately owned Swedish consultancy company Viridis IT. [ID:nL6N0RR0M8]  ** Indonesian telecommunication operator PT Smartfren Telecom Tbk <FREN.JK> is in talks with peer PT Bakrie Telecom Tbk <BTEL.JK> on a potential merger of their network operations. [ID:nL3N0RR24Y]